<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 1:59PM CDT  by NWS Austin-San Antonio</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Comal County
through 245 PM CDT...
At 159 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Canyon Lake, or near Canyon Lake Dam, moving west at 5 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Canyon Lake Dam, Canyon Lake, Bulverde, Spring Branch, Smithson
Valley, Fischer, Startzville and Sattler.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
